filter :Controles des plages horaires autorisees

abortProcessingOnLogError 0
logMask 2
generatedProperties
script importPackage(Packages.com.vordel.trace); importPackage(Packages.java.util); function invoke(msg) { //Format de la plage horaire attendu var myRegex = new java.lang.String("([0-2][0-9])[H-h]([0-5][0-9])"); //Rcupration du paramtrage contextuel // Dimanche : 1 plage par dfaut de 22h00 23h00 // Dimanche var plageHoraireDimancheDebut1Indispo = msg.get("plage.horaire.dimanche.debut.indispo.1"); var plageHoraireDimancheFin1Indispo = msg.get("plage.horaire.dimanche.fin.indispo.1"); var plageHoraireDebut1Indispo; var plageHoraireFin1Indispo; // On dtermine le jour de la semaine et l'heure courante var calNow = new GregorianCalendar(); // 1. jour de la semaine var dayOfWeek = calNow.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_WEEK); //Trace.debug("dayOfWeek : " + dayOfWeek); // 2. on fixe les plages horaires d'indisponibilit selon l'algo suivant : // plage de fermeture programme pour CPF : dimanche de 22h00 23h00 if (dayOfWeek == Calendar.SUNDAY) { plageHoraireDebut1Indispo = plageHoraireDimancheDebut1Indispo; plageHoraireFin1Indispo = plageHoraireDimancheFin1Indispo; } else { return true; } //3. on vrifie le format des paramtres //3.1 plage debut 1 var debut1Indispo = plageHoraireDebut1Indispo.match(myRegex); var debutHeure1Indispo; var debutMinute1Indispo; if (debut1Indispo != null) { //Trace.debug ("OK "+ debut1Indispo[1] + ":" + debut1Indispo[2]); debutHeure1Indispo = new java.lang.Integer(debut1Indispo[1]).intValue(); debutMinute1Indispo = new java.lang.Integer(debut1Indispo[2]).intValue(); } else { return false; } //3.2 plage fin 1 var fin1Indispo = plageHoraireFin1Indispo.match(myRegex); var finHeure1Indispo; var finMinute1Indispo; if (fin1Indispo != null) { //Trace.debug ("OK "+ fin1Indispo[1] + ":" + fin1Indispo[2]); finHeure1Indispo = new java.lang.Integer(fin1Indispo[1]).intValue(); finMinute1Indispo = new java.lang.Integer(fin1Indispo[2]).intValue(); } else { return false; } // 4. on vrifie si le flux n'est pas dans la plage horaire interdite //4.1 conversion de la plage horaire de dbut 1 en minute var debut1IndispoMIN = (debutHeure1Indispo * 60) + debutMinute1Indispo; //Trace.debug ("debut1IndispoMIN : " + debut1IndispoMIN); //4.2 conversion de la plage horaire de fin 1 en minute var fin1IndispoMIN = (finHeure1Indispo * 60) + finMinute1Indispo; //Trace.debug ("fin1IndispoMIN : " + fin1IndispoMIN); //4.5 comparaison la date systme var heureCouranteMIN = (calNow.get(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY) * 60) + calNow.get(Calendar.MINUTE); //Trace.debug ("heureCouranteMIN : " + heureCouranteMIN); if ( (heureCouranteMIN > debut1IndispoMIN && heureCouranteMIN < fin1IndispoMIN) ) { return false; } else { return true; } }
logSuccess Passed javascript filter
logFailure Failed javascript filter
requiredProperties
logMaskType SERVICE
name Controles des plages horaires autorisees
consumedProperties
engineName js
logFatal Error while attempt to run javascript filter. Error: ${circuit.exception}

script importPackage(Packages.java.security); importPackage(Packages.com.vordel.trace); importPackage(Packages.java.util); importPackage(Packages.org.apache.commons.codec.binary); function invoke(msg) { var hash, hashBytes, hashBytesLeftHalf, atHashICDC ; if (msg.get("accesstoken") == null) {return true; } else { var accessToken = new java.lang.String(msg.get("accesstoken")); Trace.debug("Access Token : " + accessToken); try { hash = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256"); hash.reset(); hash.update(accessToken.getBytes()); hashBytes = hash.digest(); Trace.debug("HASH AT : " + new java.lang.String(hashBytes)); hashBytesLeftHalf = java.util.Arrays.copyOf(hashBytes, hashBytes.length / 2); Trace.debug("LEFT HALF HASH AT : " + new java.lang.String(hashBytesLeftHalf)); atHashICDC = org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64.encodeBase64URLSafeString(hashBytesLeftHalf); Trace.debug("LEFT HALF HASH AT base64 : " + atHashICDC); msg.put("at.hash.icdc.claim", atHashICDC); return true; } catch (e) { Trace.error(">>>Exception : " +e); msg.put("at.hash.icdc.claim", ""); return true; } } }

filter :Extract End Time and Produce Trace

script //importPackage(java.util); //importClass(java.text.SimpleDateFormat); function invoke(msg) { var now = new Date(); // var df= new SimpleDateFormat("dd/MMMMM/yyyy:HH:mm:ss SSSS", Locale.FRANCE); // var dateEndDisplay = df.format(now.getTime()); var dateEndDisplay = now.toUTCString(); var startTime = msg.get("technique.stat.start"); var totalTimeMs = Math.round(parseInt(now.getTime()) - parseInt(startTime)); msg.put("request.reponse.time", totalTimeMs); var userid = msg.get("authentication.subject.id"); if (!userid) { userid = null; } else { userid = String(userid); } // Nom du path ou de l'API var apiName = msg.get("api.name"); var targetURL; if (apiName) { var serviceName = msg.get("service.name"); targetURL = serviceName + " - " + msg.get("api.method.path"); } else { targetURL = msg.get("resolved.to.path"); } // AdresseIp var ipSource = msg.get("request.ip.source"); var ipOrigin = msg.get("request.ip.origin"); if (!ipSource) { ipSource = msg.get("http.request.clientaddr"); ipOrigin = msg.get("http.request.clientaddr"); } // Rcupration d'un message d'erreur // Attention, par defaut, il y a un message d'erreur standard var detail = msg.get("msg.error.reason"); if (!detail) { detail = "Aucun dtail"; } // Extraction du code statut var codeStatus = msg.get("http.response.status") ? msg.get("http.response.status") : msg.get("msg.error.status"); if (codeStatus) { codeStatus = String(codeStatus); if (codeStatus.substring(0,1) === "2" || codeStatus.substring(0,1) ==="3" ) { detail = "Aucun dtail"; } } var trace = "TECHNIQUE#STAT_DUREE_CIRCUIT#" + dateEndDisplay + "#" + ipSource + "#" + ipOrigin + "#" + msg.get("http.request.verb") + "#" + targetURL + "#" + msg.get("id") + "#" + userid + "#" + codeStatus + "#" + totalTimeMs + "#" + detail; msg.put("trace.technique", trace); return true; }
logSuccess ${trace.technique}
logFailure Failed script filter
requiredProperties
logMaskType FILTER
name Extract End Time and Produce Trace
consumedProperties
engineName nashorn
logFatal Error while attempt to run script filter. Error: ${circuit.exception}

filter :Control of http-signature header // updated

abortProcessingOnLogError 0
logMask 2
generatedProperties
script importPackage(Packages.java.security); importPackage(Packages.com.vordel.trace); importPackage(Packages.java.util); importPackage(org.apache.commons.codec.binary.*); importPackage (java.security.*); importPackage (java.security.spec.*); importPackage (com.vordel.jose.crypto.*); function invoke(msg) { try{ //On rcupre la cl publique du certificat et le header http-signature var certificate= msg.get("certificate"); var signatureHeader= msg.get("params.header.Signature"); var paramsHeader= msg.get("params.in.header"); var contentHeaders= msg.get("http.content.headers"); var method=msg.get("http.request.method"); var uri =msg.get("http.request.rawURI"); Trace.debug("certificate :"+certificate ); if (certificate != null && certificate !='') { var publicKey = certificate.getPublicKey(); Trace.debug("publicKey :"+ publicKey ); abortProcessingOnLogError 0
logMask 2
generatedProperties
script import java.io.FileInputStream; import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream; import java.io.InputStream; import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets; import java.security.cert.CertificateExpiredException import java.security.cert.CertificateFactory; import java.security.cert.CertificateNotYetValidException import java.security.cert.X509Certificate; import com.vordel.trace.Trace; import com.vordel.common.base64.Decoder; import java.util.Map; import org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1InputStream; import org.bouncycastle.asn1.DEROctetString; import org.bouncycastle.asn1.DERSequence; import org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Sequence; import org.bouncycastle.asn1.x509.qualified.QCStatement; import org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Encodable; def invoke(msg) { def base64EncodedData = msg.get("psd2.base64certificate"); String roleStringTri = ""; if(base64EncodedData != null ){ InputStream inStream = null; try { inStream = new ByteArrayInputStream(base64EncodedData.getBytes()); Trace.debug(new String(base64EncodedData.getBytes())); CertificateFactory cf = CertificateFactory.getInstance("X.509"); X509Certificate cert = (X509Certificate)cf.generateCertificate(inStream); if (cert != null) { try { Trace.debug(cert.toString()); extensionValue= cert.getExtensionValue("1.3.6.1.5.5.7.1.3") Trace.debug(">>> extension: " + extensionValue.toString()); ASN1Sequence qcStatements; ASN1InputStream derAsn1InputStream = new ASN1InputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(extensionValue)); DEROctetString oct = (DEROctetString) derAsn1InputStream.readObject(); Trace.debug(">>> oct : " + oct ); derAsn1InputStream.close(); ASN1InputStream asn1InputStream = new ASN1InputStream(oct.getOctets()); qcStatements = (ASN1Sequence) asn1InputStream.readObject(); Trace.debug(">>> qcStatements : " + qcStatements ); asn1InputStream.close(); // Certificat CDC// //QCStatement statement = QCStatement.getInstance(qcStatements.getObjectAt(0)); //Trace.debug(">>> statement: " + statement); // Certificat Eurobits// //QCStatement statement = QCStatement.getInstance(qcStatements.getObjectAt(3)); //Trace.debug(">>> statement: " + statement); // Rajout qcStatement 0.4.0.19495.2 for ( int j = 0; j < qcStatements.size(); j++){ QCStatement statement = QCStatement.getInstance(qcStatements.getObjectAt(j)); Trace.debug(">>> statementLoop: " + statement); Trace.debug(">>> getStatementId: " + statement.getStatementId().getId()); if (statement.getStatementId().getId().contains("0.4.0.19495.2")) { Trace.debug(">>> sequenceStatementIdStringYES"); /////////// ASN1Encodable statementInfo = statement.getStatementInfo(); Trace.debug(">>> statementInfo : " + statementInfo); ASN1Sequence sequence = ASN1Sequence.getInstance(statementInfo); Trace.debug(">>> sequence : " + sequence); ASN1Sequence seqroles = ASN1Sequence.getInstance(sequence.getObjectAt(0)); Trace.debug(">>> seqroles: " + seqroles); String[] roles = new String[4]; String rolestring = null; for ( int i = 0; i < seqroles.size(); i++){ ASN1Sequence seqRole = ASN1Sequence.getInstance(seqroles.getObjectAt(i)); roles[i] = seqRole.getObjectAt(1).getString(); Trace.debug(">>> role: " + roles[i]); rolestring = rolestring + "," + seqRole.getObjectAt(1).getString(); rolestring = rolestring.replace("PSP_PI", "pisp").replace("PSP_AI", "aisp").replace("PSP_IC", "cbpii").replace("null","").replace(","," "); if (rolestring.contains("aisp")) roleStringTri = "aisp"; if (rolestring.contains("cbpii")) roleStringTri = roleStringTri + " " + "cbpii"; if (rolestring.contains("pisp")) roleStringTri = roleStringTri + " " + "pisp"; Trace.debug(">>> rolestring : " + rolestring); Trace.debug(">>> rolestringtri : " + roleStringTri); } msg.put("certificate.roles", roles); msg.put("certificate.rolestring", rolestring ); msg.put("certificate.rolestringtri", roleStringTri ); }else{ Trace.error("Le certificat ne contient pas de qcStatements valide"); } } // Fin Rajout }catch(CertificateExpiredException e1) { Trace.error("Invalid QWAC certificate. Certificate is expired"); }catch(CertificateNotYetValidException e2) { Trace.error("Invalid QWAC certificate. Certificate is not yet valid"); } } } catch(Exception e){ Trace.error (e); }finally { if (inStream != null) { inStream.close(); } } } return true; }
